webpackJsonp([0x989e9c333148],{394:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{meta:{title:"CIID Final Project Kelvyn Marte",description:"CIID Final Project Kelvyn Marte",url:"https://kelvynmarte.github.io/ciid-final-project-documentation",author:"Kelvyn Ornette Sol Marte",twitter:"kelvynmarte"}},post:{id:"/Users/kelvyn/Projects/2017_08 CIID Final Project/05 Production/Web/ciid-final-project-documentation/src/pages/introduction/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<blockquote>\n<p>66% of All Humans Will Live in Cities by 2050</p>\n<footer><cite>—UN, 2014</cite></footer>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thinking of more and more people moving to cities and the demand to have a high quality of living in increasingly dense the cities.\nI started of my research with the very broad statement of intent: <strong>understand urban metal wellbeing</strong></p>\n<p>I am inspired by some future cities projects and very interested in the social implication of the ways we live together in the future.</p>\n<p>Knowing that this is a very broad statement of intent to start with I knew that I will just have to look out for promising opportunity areas which spark my interest.</p>\n<h2>I want my Final Project to</h2>\n<p>Challenge myself in user research and iteration, I have the feeling with previous projects we usually spent a lot of time for one or the other but never both, which always felt a bit of a shortcoming. Since I enjoy building things a lot and I am a big believer in prototyping to learn but also to ideate, I definitely want to spent a good amount of my time prototyping and building.</p>\n<p>I want to feel in control of my final project as much as possible, with spending the propper amount of time on reflecting. I know already that there will be a lot of moments of uncertainty, but I want to try to always keep the momentum going and have as little moments of feeling stuck as possible.</p>\n<h2>My starting point</h2>\n<p>How can urban spaces and additions and modifications to the environment affects mental wellbeing?\nWhat can be learned from rural areas? Or different city areas of Copenhagen?</p>\n<p>To narrow my topic further down I want to form some assumptions through desk research, compare cities and come up with hypothesis which can lead my research. To get inspired and have a quick dive into the topic I plan to have some interviews with experts in combination with some observations and interviews in Copenhagen.</p>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;; max-width: 750px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 16.75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="postit timeline"\n        title=""\n        src="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-245fd.png"\n        srcset="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-7aee9.png 188w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-2014b.png 375w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-245fd.png 750w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-a0f71.png 1125w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-9b813.png 1500w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/7573c06f5b01ee47ccb64a2324980464-a3a8d.png 1600w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<p><em>Planing out my 10 weeks with post-its</em></p>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;; max-width: 750px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 57.43494423791822%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Early thoughts mind map"\n        title=""\n        src="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-245fd.png"\n        srcset="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-7aee9.png 188w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-2014b.png 375w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-245fd.png 750w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-a0f71.png 1125w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-9b813.png 1500w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-5c1b6.png 2250w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/d3e5cc03d2b4952922969e5dd9a15641-9df16.png 3766w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<em>Early thoughts mind map</em></p>\n<h2>This project is relevant because</h2>\n<p>Urban citizens increasingly suffer from mental health problems, which can range from mild depressions to schizophrenia, or arguably even cancer. While we don’t know all factors causing mental health problems, we know that one strong social connections and social capital is one of the most effective ways to prevent mental health problems. That’s why I want to explore in this project different ways to create pro-social interventions, which can facilitated at times but possibly also prevent interactions when not desired.</p>\n<h2>Early Inspirations</h2>\n<h3>Times Square Place Making / Prototyping</h3>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;; max-width: 435px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 66.64829106945976%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Times Square Place Making / Prototyping"\n        title=""\n        src="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-45920.jpg"\n        srcset="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-c3c84.jpg 188w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-d6aee.jpg 375w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-45920.jpg 750w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-71fe0.jpg 1125w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-01792.jpg 1500w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/cfec7825d233e12f34eca6e516f9a42d-307db.jpg 1814w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 435px) 100vw, 435px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  </p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.20608899297424%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem"\n          >\n            <html><head></head><body><div style="max-width:854px"><div style="position:relative;height:0;padding-bottom:56.25%"><iframe src="https://embed.ted.com/talks/janette_sadik_khan_new_york_s_streets_not_so_mean_any_more" style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          " frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen></iframe></div></div></body></html>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<h3>Regen Village</h3>\n<p>\n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem;; max-width: 750px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 60%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Regen Village"\n        title=""\n        src="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-df60d.jpg"\n        srcset="/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-45144.jpg 188w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-2f941.jpg 375w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-df60d.jpg 750w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-b1889.jpg 1125w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-1d6f8.jpg 1500w,\n/ciid-final-project-documentation/static/e06e1745239c6f6186d9f20edd6d3c45-56d51.jpg 1580w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n<em><a href="http://www.regenvillages.com/">http://www.regenvillages.com/</a></em></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.ted.com/playlists/29/our_future_in_cities">https://www.ted.com/playlists/29/our<em>future</em>in_cities</a></p>\n<h3>Transformation of cities</h3>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.20608899297424%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem"\n          >\n            <html><head></head><body><div style="max-width:854px"><div style="position:relative;height:0;padding-bottom:56.25%"><iframe src="https://embed.ted.com/talks/jaime_lerner_sings_of_the_city" style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          " frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen></iframe></div></div></body></html>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Cities are not a problem, they are a solution, to climate change …</p>\n<footer><cite>Jaime Lerner, 2007</cite></footer>\n</blockquote>\n<h3>Lauren Mccarthy, Tools for Improved Social Interacting</h3>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class="gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper"\n            style="padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem"\n          >\n            <html><head></head><body><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/8549273" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen="" mozallowfullscreen="" allowfullscreen style="\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          "></iframe></body></html>\n          </div>\n          </div>\n<!---\nIn understanding urban mental well-being of (adults/teenagers).\nHow can urban spaces and additions and modifications to the environment affects mental health?\nWhat can be learned from rural areas? Or different city areas of Copenhagen?\n\nOne comprehensive source of information around the topic I found at:\nhttp://www.urbandesignmentalhealth.com/facts-and-figures.html\nhttp://lauren-mccarthy.com/Social-Turkers\nhttp://lauren-mccarthy.com/Relatable\nhttp://lauren-mccarthy.com/Tools-for-Improved-Social-Interacting\n-->',frontmatter:{layout:"post",title:"Introduction",path:"/introduction/",categories:["Typography","TESTS"],date:"2016/03/01"}}},pathContext:{path:"/introduction/"}}}});
